The University Cafeteria Pre-Order System is designed to help students order food before break time, avoid long queues, and check if food is still available. The system has different parts that work together: the student interface, staff interface, order management, payment handling, food availability management, notification system, and database.

A) UML Diagram
https://lucid.app/lucidchart/af3c90a8-6568-4788-8f05-83e6f455d18d/edit?invitationId=inv_5efb1c7b-35c2-4beb-8ecb-e0aebc16f9e0

Left side of the diagram:
Smart Cafeteria System: is the main system that connects all components to each other and controls the overall operation.
Components (middle part):
User Management: manages user information and login to the system.
Menu Management: manages the cafeteria menu and available products.
Order Management: deals with the creation and processing of orders from users.
Pickup Slot Management: manages the times when orders can be picked up by customers/students.
Notification Management: sends notifications about order status or changes in the system.
Report Management: creates reports on orders, users, and cafeteria operations.

Right side of the diagram:
Security: controls system security, user access, and data protection.
Persistence: maintains data in the system and ensures that information is not lost.
Cafeteria Database: is the database where user data, menus, orders, and reports are stored.
Data Access: shows the connection that reads and writes data from the database. This component helps other components retrieve or store information in the database.

